Some data structures
======================

-  Vectors (numbers)
-  You can apply functions over entire vectors (vectorization)

```{r vector}
a <- c(3, 5, 3, 7, 10)
b = c(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)
1/b
sum((a-mean(a))^2)/(length(a)-1)
var(a)
```

Sequences
============

You can construct a sequence like a for loop

```{r sequence}
seq(-5, 5, by=2)
seq(-5, 5, 2)
```

Functions
=========
And group operations into functions

```{r functions}

sortplot <- function(x, y){
  x <- sort(x)
  y <- sort(y)
  plot(x,y)
  abline(lm(y~x))
}
sortplot(a,b)
```

